Evolved Sampling with context applied to the image SD models to drecrease memory requirements "Unsampler - Custom Sampler' and RAVE.

This allows processing more frames than with the originals.

Hands up for Kijai for this trick
Choose one of the Depth preprocessors
Depending on the type of animation, values between 8-14 have worked well.
Depending on the video resolution,  number of frames, speed video, machine, etc. I have used 512- 960 px

Typically every 2nd frame works fine.
Max. every 4th. Every frame is also ok, but longer render times.

Remember to adjust framerates videos according to this value
NSFW, bad quality, worst quality, watermark, 2D cartoon
POS PROMPT: Add keywords describing features to 'help' the animation to render what you want
(3d style), (3D rendering), (3D character), octane,C4D,blender,depth, green eyes

STEP 1: PREPARATION AND KEYFRAME SELECTION
LOAD MODELS (CKPT, VAE, AD) AND LOAD VIDEO
SET CAP FRAME LIMIT, FRAME WIDTH and Select every nth (frame)
SET PROCESS ALL FRAMES = TRUE
SET RENDER GROUPS ACTOVE =  "no" for GROUPS 2A/B/C/D
(KEYFRAME AND NUMBER TESTING FRAMES DO NOTHING IF ALL FRAMES IS TRUE))
RUN 
CHOOSE WHICH of the frames (in the FRAMES preview) will be your keyframe.
The KEYFRAME number will be the frame number -1
---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

STEP 2: TUNING REFERENCE KEYFRAME
SET PROCESS ALL FRAMES = FALSE
SET KEYFRAME = KEYFRAME number (from the previous step)
SET NUMBER OF TESTING FRAMES = 1
SET RENDER GROUPS MUTER =  "YES" for GROUPS 2A/B/C/D
FINE TUNE CN, PROMPT AND CFGs (for the Keyframe) until image generated is satisfactory
---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

STEP 3: TUNING SHORT ANIMATION CLIP
PROCESS ALL FRAMES = FALSE
KEEP SAME KEYFRAME NUMBER 
SET NUMBER OF TESTING FRAMES = 10 (recommended to confirm/refine in a 2nd step with 32)
KEEP RENDER GROUPS MUTER = "YES" for GROUPS 2A/B/C/D
FINE TUNE CN, PROMPT and CFGs FOR A SMALL SET OF FRAMES
*Optional: try for different keyframe for extreme finetuning
---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

STEP 4: RENDER COMPLETE ANIMATION
PROCESS ALL FRAMES = TRUE
SET RENDER GROUPS MUTER =  "YES" for GROUPS 2A/B/C/D
(KEYFRAME AND NUMBER TESTING FRAMES DO NOTHING IF ALL FRAMES IS TRUE)

ADJUST FINE-TUNNING IF NEEDED (DEPENDING ON RENDER TIME, MAYBE GO BACK TO STEP 4)
IF YOU WANT TO SAVE THE VIDEOS, REMEMBER TO ACTIVATE THE SAVE OPTION IN THE VIDEO COMBINE NODES

FINETUNING RECOMMENDATIONS
-------------------------------------------
WHAT DO YOU NEED TO FINETUNE?
I recommend to vary
- ControlNet Strengths (Lineart, Depth and Color)
- Type of Depth Map preprocessor (Midas, Leres, Zoe, Depth Anything, Zoe Depth Anything)
- CFG RAVE Ksampler
- Add/change keywords in the positive prompt

You may also want to vary end percents in the CNs. The models being used, the width (resolution) of the video and the selection of frames also have an effect.

I have not tested all possible variations and try to limit what needs to change, but feel free to experiment. Lineart has provided me with best results, but I do not see why other edge detectors cannot work (depending on the outcome you want, can be nice to play). IP Adapters at low strength may also help, but I have done very limited testing.

HOW TO FINETUNE?
So far, my experience is that different settings are required for different animations. These are my learnings:
- CFG RAVE KSampler: I recommend to start with 8, and start increasing until the desired effect can be observed. Too high, the image will be burnt and may hallucinate. Too low, and the image will be too similar to the original
- DEPTH PREPROCESSOR: Depending on the scene/video, you may want to use different preprocessors. This is a little bit of trial and error.
- COLOR STRENGTH: The higher the value, the closer color adherence to the original image. However, too high number may also lead to hallucinations and too much color bleeding.
- DEPTH STRENGTH: The higher the value, the more 3D effect, but too high may lead to some small artifacts and flickering.
- LINEAR STRENGTH: Needs to be balanced. Too high, the result will be more similar to the original. Too low, more color bleeding and may hallucinate
- PROMPT: addition of some keywords may help, e.g. using the color of hair and eyes. However, too many details may 'confuse' the RAVE model and make the image to show some things which are not in the original.


RECOMMENDED RANGES:
Strength Lineart CN: 0.5-0.8
Strength Depth CN: 0.5-0.8
Aux preprocessor Depth: All Depth preprocessors (not mesh graphormer!)
Strength Color CN: 0.4-1
CFG: 8-14

USE 0 to process all frames.
Select a number between 10-100 for to choose a keyframe.
For OpenArt, use a lower number (for example 32), otherwise you will not have time to render everything.
